# Backend Architecture

> See also: `core.mdc` · `api.mdc` · `prisma.mdc` · `core/architecture.mdc` (SOLID, SRP, KISS, DRY)

## Dependency Flow

Strict top-down dependencies only:

```
Controller → Use Case → Repository → Prisma
```

### Allowed

- Controller imports and calls Use Case (via `@/application/[module]`)
- Use Case imports Repository interface (via `@/domain/[module]`)
- Repository implementation imports Prisma Client

### Forbidden

- Use Case importing NestJS decorators, HTTP types, or Prisma
- Repository containing business logic
- Controller accessing Prisma or Repository directly
- Skipping layers (Controller → Repository)
- Deep file imports (see `core.mdc`)

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer          | Responsibility                               | Must NOT                          |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| **Controller** | HTTP handling, DTO mapping, calling Use Case | Business logic, database access   |
| **Use Case**   | Business rules and orchestration             | Depend on NestJS, Prisma, or HTTP |
| **Repository** | Data access and persistence mapping          | Business logic, HTTP concerns     |
| **Prisma**     | Database queries (via Repository only)       | Business decisions                |

## Use Case Rules

- All business logic lives **only** in Use Cases
- Use Cases are plain TypeScript classes — no NestJS imports, decorators, or Prisma inside the class
- Accept input as plain types or domain objects — not NestJS DTOs
- Return domain results or throw domain exceptions

The Use Case **class** stays framework-agnostic. NestJS wires it via `providers` in a module — that registration lives in `presentation/` or `infrastructure/`, not inside the Use Case file.

```ts
// ✅ Use Case — plain TypeScript, repository interface only
export class CreateTodoUseCase {
  constructor(private readonly todoRepository: TodoRepository) {}

  async execute(input: CreateTodoInput): Promise<Todo> {
    // business logic here
  }
}

// ❌ — Prisma or NestJS inside the Use Case class
export class CreateTodoUseCase {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}
}
```

## Repository Rules

- One repository per aggregate or entity group
- Expose an interface (port) in `domain/`; implement in `infrastructure/`
- Map Prisma models to domain entities inside the repository

## Folder Structure

```
apps/server/src/
├── domain/
│   └── todo/
│       ├── todo.entity.ts
│       ├── todo.repository.ts
│       └── index.ts
├── application/
│   └── create-todo/
│       ├── create-todo.use-case.ts
│       └── index.ts
├── infrastructure/
│   └── todo/
│       ├── prisma-todo.repository.ts
│       └── index.ts
└── presentation/
    └── todo/
        ├── todo.controller.ts
        ├── dto/
        └── index.ts
```

## Code Organization

- Prefer small functions with a single responsibility (see `core/architecture.mdc` SRP)
- No magic strings or numbers — use `constants.ts` (see `core/code-style.mdc`)
- Do not duplicate logic — extract shared code into domain or application helpers (DRY)
